  {
    "@type": "Event",
    "name": "The Autorickshaw Project",
    "url": "https://puttingscene.com/events/5168",
    "startDate": "2026-07-17T16:00:00+05:30",
    "endDate": "2026-07-17T18:00:00+05:30",
    "description": "<p>Bengaluru's autorickshaws have always been more than a way to get around. They carry conversations, neighbourhood stories and everyday moments that make the city what it is.</p><p><strong>The Autorickshaw Project by Foodstories</strong> is a collaboration with a collective of passionate artists from across India, bringing the finest food stories to one of Bengaluru's most iconic symbols. Together, we've transformed autorickshaws into moving canvases, each inspired by the ingredients, flavours and stories that define Foodstories.</p><p>For one evening, Foodstories becomes a celebration of food, art and culture. From <strong>The City as a Canvas</strong>, a panel discussion featuring <strong>Malini Malik</strong>, Founder of General Items, <strong>Artist Seema Surana</strong>, and <strong>Artist Ankita D'Souza</strong>, to ingredient-led experiences, inventive coffee tastings, hot sauce tastings by <strong>The Wild Jar</strong>, and unexpected discoveries across the store, every experience is designed to spark curiosity and invite you to experience familiar ingredients in entirely new ways.</p><p>Come for the art, stay for the conversations, and experience Bengaluru through food, creativity and community.</p>",
    "image": "https://cdn.puttingscene.com/event_images/5168/37e3f3e0-13c5-43da-8163-9d4c47ec2bac.jpg",
    "location": {
      "name": "Foodstories, Bangalore",
      "address": "Foodstories, Bangalore, Bangalore",
      "url": "https://maps.app.goo.gl/hZadDqwRRYsHweDo8"
    },
    "isAccessibleForFree": true
  },
